  "body": "Phase D D1 merged (PR #20, commit 32260be, build 14). REST + OpenAPI transport ships at /api/... mirroring the six-tool MCP surface; shared impls in server/tool_impls.py prevent drift. **Cross-vendor demo achieved with a surprise**: ChatGPT shipped native MCP Connectors support — Director registered the bare MCP URL (not the OpenAPI URL we built) and ChatGPT authenticated as personal-strategist via PIN ceremony, then filed a memo-to-file readable from Claude sessions. The REST adapter we built turned out to be unnecessary for THIS demonstration; still useful for legacy Custom GPT Actions, scripts, and non-MCP OpenAPI consumers. Five vendors now confirmed MCP-native (Claude Code/Desktop/mobile, Perplexity, ChatGPT). Body_ref has the disposition, Phase E/F starting context, the C7 reminder, and notes for the cross-vendor experience memo I'm filing to roledef-strategist.",
